contentrichtext.text: '''James McMillan''' may refer to: * [[James McMillan (fur trader)]] (1783–1858), founder of Fort Langley, British Columbia * [[James W. McMillan]] (1825–1903), Union officer during the American Civil War * [[James McMillan (politician)]] (1838–1902), U.S. Senator from Michigan * [[James McMillan (footballer)]] (born c. 1866), played for Sunderland * [[James McMillan (Scottish footballer)]], played for Notts County * [[James Bryan McMillan]] (1916–1995), U.S. federal judge * [[Jim McMillan (politician)]] (born c. 1933), Canadian fringe politician * [[Jim McMillan (speedway rider)]] (born 1945), Scottish motorcycle speedway rider * [[Jimmy McMillan]] (born 1946), U.S. fringe politician, founder of The Rent Is Too Damn High Party * [[James Francis McMillan]] (1948–2010), Scottish historian and author * [[James MacMillan]] (born 1959), Scottish composer * [[James McMillan (cricketer)]] (born 1978), New Zealand cricketer {{hndis|McMillan, James}}
